hire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1150–":"about 1150–Deceased","1150–Male":"1150–Deceased","1155–Female":"1155–Deceased","1175–Female":"1175–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1125–Male":"1125–Deceased","1120–Female":"1120–Deceased","about 1150":"about 1150","1125":"1125","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Saltmarsh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Essex): from Middle English <i>salt-mareis</i> ‘salt-marsh’. The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived on or by a salt-marsh, or habitational from a place so named, such as Saltmarshe (East Yorkshire; Herefordshire), Saltmarsh in Henbury (Gloucestershire), or Salt Marsh in Hailsham (Sussex)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Saltmarsh was born about 1150, in Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Saltmarsh, was 27 and his mother, Child Metham, was 32. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Grace Luddington. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1150–":"umbes 1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1125":"1125","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1150–":"noin 1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1125":"1125","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1150–":"environ 1150–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1125–Male":"1125–Décédé","1120–Female":"1120–Décédée","about 1150":"environ 1150","1125":"1125","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Saltmarsh est né environ 1150, à Ingoldsby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, John Saltmarsh, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Child Metham, avait 32 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Grace Luddington. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"about 1150–":"um 1150–Verstorben","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorben","1175–Female":"1175–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1125–Male":"1125–Verstorben","1120–Female":"1120–Verstorben","about 1150":"um 1150","1125":"1125","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","Ingoldsb